The paper deals with approximation algorithms for a generalization of the bin packing problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT) to develop the approximation schemes. Additionally, the paper involves mathematical programming and optimization (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT) in its analysis.
